Additionally, the paper discusses the dynamics of opinion spreading models, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The study of threshold effects and the use of techniques that may be of independent value suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. Finally, the fact that the paper deals with distributed systems and convergence properties could make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
